      <elementaryExchange id="9868f9e7-e277-5601-8fc2-32a2c7eb05cc" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000124-38-9" amount="0.27962" elementaryExchangeId="f9749677-9c9f-4678-ab55-c607dfdc2cb9" formula="CO2">
        <name xml:lang="en">Carbon dioxide, fossil</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The remaining amount of unreacted benzyl chloride and benzyl cyanide is assumed to leave the production process with the waste water, also the remaining amount of produced ammonia. Further it was assumed that this wastewater is treated in a internal wastewater plant. The removal efficiency for benzyl chloride and benzyl cyanide is assumed with 100%. The carbon contained in the removed benzyl chloride and benzyl cyanide is accounted as CO2 emissions to air.</comment>
